[{"descriptions":["For now, algorithm is to be kept fairly simple. A \"right\" swipe will give a user 10 points. A \"left\" swipe gives a user 0 points. The user's rating is their total points divided by total swipe.","As an example, a user who had received 8 swipe right and 2 swipes left would have a rating of 8.0 (10[points per swipe]*8[swipes right] / 10[total swipe] * 10.0 [turns decimal into rating out of 10).","System will be built in modular manner so that in the future, the \"rating calculation\" aspect of the program can be easily swapped out for new, more advanced logic without disrupting other parts of the application."],"display":"Users are provided a rating (0-10) based off of our own algorithm","title":"Users are provided a rating (0-10) based off of our own algorithm"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Users rate at the time that they view someone's card (while swiping left or right)","title":"Users rate at the time that they view someone's card (while swiping left or right)"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Standard Tinder features included (chat, left/right swipe mechanic, tinder-style matching...)","title":"Standard Tinder features included (chat, left/right swipe mechanic, tinder-style matching...)"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Paying users can limit their results to users who have acquired a high average rating from the community of users","title":"Paying users can limit their results to users who have acquired a high average rating from the community of users"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Client to provide wireframes","title":"Client to provide wireframes"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Gigster to provide simple UI designs","title":"Gigster to provide simple UI designs"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Backend to be implemented with Parse","title":"Backend to be implemented with Parse"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Client to be implemented with Swift, NOT Objective-C","title":"Client to be implemented with Swift, NOT Objective-C"}]

column7: [{"descriptions":["Design for user experience and product functionality"],"display":"Wireframes","title":"Wireframes"},{"descriptions":["Mockups for the user interface of the product"],"display":"Production Design","title":"Production Design"},{"descriptions":["User accounts sign up (Digits)"],"display":"Accounts","title":"Accounts"},{"descriptions":["tour guides have a profile with basic information (profile photo, first name, tourism certifications).","There is also a 5 star rating system will be used to rate tour guides following every live stream tour. The prospective viewers of the tour will be given an opportunity to rate the tour guides out of 5 stars after a live stream comes to an end. The tour guides overall average ratings out of 5 stars will be shown under the tour guides profile section.","Users (tourists) of the app have a profile with their basic information ( from the user sign profile (like name and email address)","The User profiles will have a section where the live tour video streams that they have viewed will be saved in their entirety under their profile for 24 hours. The Users can download these videos to their phones camera roll within those 24 hours. This feature is similar to Periscope."],"display":"Profiles","title":"Profiles"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Kickflip is used as SDK for live streaming.","title":"Kickflip is used as SDK for live streaming."},{"descriptions":["Rating and review functionality as described above in profiles"],"display":"Ratings and Reviews","title":"Ratings and Reviews"},{"descriptions":["Users can search and select the city they wish to have a live stream tour from. The app will need to have a list of all the universities where campus tour guides have signed up with the app."],"display":"Simple Search","title":"Simple Search"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"\u003e displayed as the youvisit.com website / feed with infinity scroll, not as a dropdown menu","title":"\u003e displayed as the youvisit.com website / feed with infinity scroll, not as a dropdown menu"},{"descriptions":["After finding the city from the search results, the Users can then select two options. 1st option: General Tour; or 2nd option: Custom Request. For the custom request, the user will be given a text field to describe the specific type of tour he/she prefers. This custom request will be sent along with the push notification to a tour guide at the specific city or attraction (user selects specific guide from the feed, selects based on rating, specifics)","If the User selects a â€˜Custom Requestâ€™ tour, then a notification will be automatically sent out to a tour guide on the specific location (selection as above); and then the tour guide can respond to the appâ€™s tour request by selecting how soon they can start the live stream tour (example- 15 minutes from when the request is made; or 30 minutes from when the request is made; or 45 minutes from when the request is made, or 1 hour from when the request is made; or set a specific time when they can launch the live stream custom request tour. (picker view)","The User will then receive a push notification with the earliest time slot and the User can then choose and schedule the time based on these time slots that the User received from the tour guides. (select 1)","For all â€˜General Tourâ€™ requests, the User must select a 1-on-1 live stream general tour (priced at $10/tour)","If the User selects a 1-on-1 general tour ($10/tour), a push notification will sent out to a tour guide at the specific location. The tour guide can respond to the appâ€™s tour request by selecting how soon they can start the live stream tour (example- 15 minutes from when the request is made; or 30 minutes from when the request is made; or 45 minutes from when the request is made, or 1 hour from when the request is made; or set a specific time when they can launch the live stream custom request tour. When the customer opens the app they login through email or Facebook. Once they have logged in once, the app automatically logs them in every time after that.","title":"1.       When the customer opens the app they login through email or Facebook. Once they have logged in once, the app automatically logs them in every time after that."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"2.       The customer then goes through 3 or 4 pages of search criteria to narrow down the type of products they are looking for. One page might focus on the type of product (clothes, electronics, books). Depending on their selection the next few pages are customized to further narrow down their preference. For example if they choose clothes, the next few criteria screen might be, type of clothes (pants, shirts, skirts, etc), followed by colour (light, dark neutral, etc) follow by style (checks, stripe, plain).","title":"2.       The customer then goes through 3 or 4 pages of search criteria to narrow down the type of products they are looking for. One page might focus on the type of product (clothes, electronics, books). Depending on their selection the next few pages are customized to further narrow down their preference. For example if they choose clothes, the next few criteria screen might be, type of clothes (pants, shirts, skirts, etc), followed by colour (light, dark neutral, etc) follow by style (checks, stripe, plain)."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"3.       Each of the search criteria earlier will be tagged to a product in our database. Once they have chosen the criteria, products will start showing up 1 at time (like Tinder) from our database. If they click on the photo of the product that shows up, it will allow them to see other photos of the product (like Tinder). If they like the product, they swipe right and it gets stored in some sort of watchlist, if they donâ€™t like the product they swipe left.","title":"3.       Each of the search criteria earlier will be tagged to a product in our database. Once they have chosen the criteria, products will start showing up 1 at time (like Tinder) from our database. If they click on the photo of the product that shows up, it will allow them to see other photos of the product (like Tinder). If they like the product, they swipe right and it gets stored in some sort of watchlist, if they donâ€™t like the product they swipe left."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"4.       Once they have finished swiping, they can go to the watchlist, and when they click on the product it will automatically direct them through to the store where they can buy it. For one product the store might be Amazon, for another it might be Alibaba.","title":"4.       Once they have finished swiping, they can go to the watchlist, and when they click on the product it will automatically direct them through to the store where they can buy it. For one product the store might be Amazon, for another it might be Alibaba."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"We are a shopping aggregator so no physical transactions will happen through us, we will merely direct customers to the websites of other online shopping companies. [{"descriptions":["It's \"what's going on tonight?"],"display":"What is the most commonly question ask by everyone in the world right before the weekend hits?"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Well, how bout the \"iParty\" app can answer that for you."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"This app is design for you to find out the most popular spot in the city that you want to be at. It promotes the top clubs, bars, lounges and events in each city."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"A brand new social media tip to find out what's the best spot that night, who will be there, and how you can connect with other users in that city!"},{"descriptions":[],"display":"If you purchase the app you are able to talk with any \"iParty\" user in any city, but if not, you are limited to the users in the city you are in. \"iParty\" works by finding the most popular spot in the area, based on the amount of \"likes or check-in's\" users click for a specific spot they will be attending."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"So, it let's ppl know the attention each spot gets, what is going on but more importantly who parties where."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"A user can view each popular spots profile page to read the review, see what specials they are offering that night, and if there will be any performances or special guest attending."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"As a user, you have a profile with a picture, age, videos, comment tab and other details that you want people to see."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Once you select one of the top 10 popular places to party in the city."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Ppl can then like other users or any category they have chosen's profile to have the chance to connect with ppl with similar partying interests."},{"descriptions":[],"display":"Also, if your a private person, but just want to come out and enjoy the fun you have that option to just select what place you \"like\" or \"check-in\" and no one will know it's you. You simple select anonymous and your profile is closed to public also your location is turned off."}]

[{"descriptions":[],"display":"Two account types: service providers and customers"},{"descriptions":["Service providers are invited to the service via email, login with email + password they create from invite","Service providers can create hours where they will be available for massages"],"display":"Service Providers"},{"descriptions":["Customers login using your Google App account (@justin.tv or @twitch.tv only). First login creates account.","Hours have a start time and date, a number of appointments, an appointment length, and a location (room from a fixed list of possible rooms)","Service providers can see their recent previous and upcoming hours.","Hours cannot be created in the same room at overlapping times","Customers see a booking interface when they login with all the service provider hours for the current and next month that have available appointments, with the service provider's name.","A customer can book any available appointment with one click.","A customer can unbook an appointment with one click. They get their point back if they unbook.","A customer can book at most one appointment before the 1st of the month","A customer can book at most two appointments per month","A customer can indicate if they would like to receive email when an appointment is unbooked on short notice.","If the customer indicates this, they will receive an email letting them know whenever an appointment is unbooked less than 24 hours before it comes up.","New customers start with a point score of zero. Each massage they book decrements their points by one. Each month, everyone gains one point.","Massage appointments in service provider slots become available to be booked by a customer on the third Friday of every month for the following month.","For each point, you gain access to the booking interface a day earlier. For each negative point, a day later.","After an appointment, a customer can review the appointment.","A review is 1-5 stars and an optional comment, these reviews are visible only to admins and not to the service provider","The customer should get an email reminding them to rate the service provider","When the customer returns to the app to book, if they haven't rated their last appointment, they must do so at that time before they can proceed.","Customer accounts can be admin accounts"],"display":"Customers"},{"descriptions":["Admin can invite service providers (giving a name and email), view all feedback and bookings, and disable service provider accounts","Admins can create other admins, and can also remove other admin privileges from other customers","Admins can approve service provider hours for release to all customers for booking","Admins can edit attributes of service provider hours","Admins can view reviews for any service provider","Admins can edit the list of available rooms"],"display":"Admin"}]
